Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. In mixer, combine flour and sugar; add butter and egg yolk; blend until combined. Mix in coconut. Press dough into greased 13x9-inch glass baking dish. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until edge of crust is golden brown. Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F. With mixer, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs; mix until just combined. Stir in lime juice. Pour batter over crust. Once oven has cooled to 350 degrees F, bake 17 to 22 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Serve with toppings. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.